Document: ProgressBar
Path: godot/classes/class_progressbar.rst
Summary: Defines the base properties and functionality for progress bar nodes in Godot.

ProgressBar

Inherits: Range < CanvasItem < Node < Object

A progress bar is a graphical element used to show the progress of an operation. It displays a bar that fills up as the operation progresses.

Properties:
    value (float): The current value of the progress bar. This value is clamped between min_value and max_value. Default: 0.0
    min_value (float): The minimum possible value for the progress bar. Default: 0.0
    max_value (float): The maximum possible value for the progress bar. Default: 1.0
    step (float): The value increment/decrement when using the step method. Default: 0.1
    orientation (Orientation): The orientation of the progress bar. Can be vertical or horizontal. Default: horizontal
    show_percentage (bool): If true, the percentage value will be displayed on the progress bar. Default: false
    use_rounded_corners (bool): If true, the progress bar will use rounded corners. Default: false
    texture_under (Texture2D): Texture to draw behind the progress bar.
    texture_over (Texture2D): Texture to draw over the progress bar.
    texture_progress (Texture2D): Texture to draw for the progress part of the bar.

Methods:
    step(): Increments the value by the step amount.

Enums:
    Orientation { HORIZONTAL = 0, VERTICAL = 1 }
