Path: godot/classes/class_progressbar.rst
Summary: Describes the properties of the ProgressBar node in Godot Engine.

Property: editor_preview_indeterminate
Type: bool
Description: If false, the indeterminate animation will be paused in the editor.
Setters: set_editor_preview_indeterminate(value: bool)
Getters: is_editor_preview_indeterminate_enabled()

Property: fill_mode
Type: int
Description: The fill direction. See FillMode for possible values.
Default: 0
Setters: set_fill_mode(value: int)
Getters: get_fill_mode()

Property: indeterminate
Type: bool
Description: When set to true, the progress bar indicates that something is happening with an animation, but does not show the fill percentage or value.
Default: false
Setters: set_indeterminate(value: bool)
Getters: is_indeterminate()

Property: show_percentage
Type: bool
Description: If true, the fill percentage is displayed on the bar.
Default: true
Setters: set_show_percentage(value: bool)
Getters: is_percentage_shown()
